<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ideffdb140-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7111"><num value="7111">§ 7111.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="ideffdb141-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7111/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated for each fiscal year such sums as are necessary to carry out this chapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="ideffdb142-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7111/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Administrative expenses</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Funds appropriated under subsection (a) shall not be available for payment of the expenses or expenditures of the Board in administering any provision of any order issued under this chapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="ideffdb143-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/407/s12">Pub. L. 103–407, § 12</ref>, <date date="1994-10-22">Oct. 22, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/4226">108 Stat. 4226</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
